    "The average cycle length thus measures the mean length (i.e., number of edges) of the cycles.",
    "When there is a single cycle (as in Fig. 1), the average is the same as the length of this cycle (3).",
    "Finally, the average distance measures the mean smallest number of edges required to go between every pair of nodes.",
    "The measurements should be contextualized given the expected values for causal maps (Giabbanelli, Rice, et al., 2022).",
    "These maps are usually small-to mid-sized, under 100 nodes."
